Where do I even begin…as I start to think about the last 9 years I have a lot of emotions running thru me. I came to Boston as a naive kid from Dallas not really knowing what to expect. All I knew was the type of work ethic my momma instilled in me and I was going to work my ass off and make sure I EARNED the respect of each and every one of the fans in Boston. Which is why this was tuff. Boston, you are a very special place to me. I grew up here and met some of my best friends here. I’ll never forget my time here. Ultimately we didn’t get that 18th banner but I’m VERY VERY proud of the success we had.  I’m going to miss so many things about Boston  but mainly my teammates,  fans,  and kids and our hospital  charity work. 
It was a great 9 years Boston, thank you for all the love…but now it’s time to look forward.

 I can’t wait to get to Memphis and get started. We have something special brewing here! Am blessed to be a part of Grizzly nation. Let’s get to work. 💪🏾

#Sponsored I love traveling the world with my wife and our two dogs...they literally come everywhere with us! When we travel, we always find somewhere warm to go as we love being outside as much as we can. And this means, I have to think ahead about how the elements outdoors could impact my breathing.
The third week in September (now!) has come to be known as #AsthmaPeakWeek due to a rise in asthma attacks. That's because common asthma triggers like ragweed, mold from fallen leaves, and exposure to respiratory viruses increase during this time of the year. Since being outside is important to our family, we’re happy to partner with @astrazeneca to help educate about the #2sides2asthma attacks: airway tightening and airway inflammation. Both contribute to asthma symptoms such as shortness of breath, chest tightness, wheezing, and coughing.
Asthma can truly interfere with your daily life so I am excited to provide helpful resources that raise awareness about asthma flare-ups that are common at this time of the year. By tapping the link in my bio, you can learn more about the 2 sides 2 an asthma attack and talk to your doctor about asthma and treatment options that may be appropriate for you. #AstraZenecaPartner

#sponsored I’ve been playing golf for a few years now and my game has come a long way in a short amount of time, but I still have some work to do! My two favorite things about golf are the competitive aspect of it but even more than that I enjoy just being outside and playing 18 with my friends and family.
I have to really manage my surroundings both on and off the court in order for me to optimize my breathing. Unfortunately, there are many environmental factors that can trigger an asthma attack – especially this time of year – which means even relaxing on the golf course could cause symptoms to flare. Asthma attacks are serious and when they happen, there are 2 things that occur: airway tightening and inflammation. Having a rescue inhaler on hand is critical, however current ones may only treat airway tightening.
In partnership with @astrazeneca , I’m happy to help educate others about the #2sides2asthma . Tap the link in my bio to learn more and talk to your doctor about asthma and treatment options that may be appropriate for you. #AstraZenecaPartner #asthmapeakweek
